{"text": " Welcome to this introductory practice. Please find yourself a suitable and comfortable location. It is better if the light is not too bright at this moment. See if your location is safe and secure from any disturbance. Keep your back straight. Familiarize yourself with your surroundings. Identify your precise location exactly where you are. Be gentle with yourself and kindly accept whatever feelings emerge during this practice. Use your mind, heart and energy of your total being. Be kind to this body that you are about to observe. Allow your eyes to relax and rest your gaze downward. Covered at a 45 degree angle approximately. So that your eyes are relaxed. Next, find a spot where your eyes can stabilize. Your eyes, their gaze. The purpose of this practice is to stabilize. Recognize yourself presence and your mind while keeping the eyes open and resting peacefully. In this safe and comfortable location. Without concentrating. Allow your eyes to peacefully and passively gaze downward. Without applying any strong focus. Simply passively observe downward and start sensing your breathing. Your attention gently moves towards the breathing observation. Allow your eyes to passively gaze downward. While you are beginning to observe your breathing body. Observe your breathing process. When thoughts arise, shift your mind towards the breathing process. Allow your eyes to continue resting peacefully and observing downward without any concentration. A passive gaze. While you are observing your breathing body. Observe how your body is breathing. Exhaling, inhaling. You are peacefully observing your breathing. If you wish to close your eyes, you may do so. While you are continuing to observe your breathing body. Did you observe the breathing body? Notice how the body is breathing. Notice any sensations arising in your body. Without reacting. Continuing the observation of your breathing body. With eyes opened in a relaxed fashion. With eyes closed, you continue to observe the breathing body. With eyes opened in a relaxed fashion. You may hear the sounds around you if any. While you are peacefully resting in your location. Your eyes are not engaging with anything. You may notice how the body is breathing by itself. You are just a spectator of this peaceful process. You are the observer of how the body is breathing by itself. How everything is happening by itself. You are just simply present without doing anything. You are just simply present without doing anything. Witness the natural breathing of the body. Relax and witness this moment. You are relaxed and peaceful. Observer. Observer of your breathing body. Of this moment. This body. This moment. Thank you. Thank you.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 10.44, "end": 14.24, "text": " Welcome to this introductory practice.", "tokens": [50364, 4027, 281, 341, 39048, 3124, 13, 51300], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.3148139544895717, "compression_ratio": 1.1162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 0.0487004853785038, "words": [{"word": " Welcome", "start": 10.44, "end": 11.84, "probability": 0.7301856875419617}, {"word": " to", "start": 11.84, "end": 12.36, "probability": 0.9782800078392029}, {"word": " this", "start": 12.36, "end": 12.6, "probability": 0.9884350299835205}, {"word": " introductory", "start": 12.6, "end": 13.4, "probability": 0.9813377857208252}, {"word": " practice.", "start": 13.4, "end": 14.24, "probability": 0.9810969829559326}]}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 18.72, "end": 25.08, "text": " Please find yourself a suitable and comfortable location.", "tokens": [51300, 2555, 915, 1803, 257, 12873, 293, 4619, 4914, 13, 51810], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.3148139544895717, "compression_ratio": 1.1162790697674418, "no_speech_prob": 0.0487004853785038, "words": [{"word": " Please", "start": 18.060000000000002, "end": 18.76, "probability": 0.9740915894508362}, {"word": " find", "start": 18.76, "end": 19.18, "probability": 0.9609200358390808}, {"word":